name: Classic Black Beans and Rice
prepTime: 15 minutes
cookTime: 20 minutes
portions: 4
caloriesPerPortion: 340

ingredients:
  - (1 cup) white rice
  - (1 tsp) chicken buillon
  - (2 tb) frozen peas
  - (2 tb) olive oil
  - (1) onion, finely chopped
  - (1) green pepper, finely chopped
  - (1/2) Habanero pepper, finely chopped
  - (2 cloves) garlic, minced
  - (15.5oz can) Goya Black Beans (undrained)
  - (3/4 cup) water
  - (1 tsp) Oregano
  - (1 packet) Sazon Goya without Annatto
  - (1 tb) white wine
 
steps:
  - Cook rice in chicken stock with peas
  - Meanwhile, dice and saute onion, pepper, and garlic over
    medium-high heat in a pot until tender, about 8-10 minutes
  - Stir in remaining ingredients, and bring to a boil
  - Reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes
  - Serve over rice
